This paper deals with the automated techniques for finding errors in ASP programs, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of minimal correction sets is related to logic and reasoning, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the non-monotonic behavior of correction sets, which is a topic in propositional logic (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of program consistency, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the experimental evaluation involves machine learning algorithms, which is a subfield of deep learning (cs.DL).
